 "overview": "\u003Cp\u003EPerimeter eSecurity, Inc. provides on demand security services for computer networks in the United States. It offers intrusion defense solutions, such as firewall, intrusion detection and prevention, and Web browsing anti-virus; and email defense solutions, including Microsoft hosted exchange services, email archiving and compliance, anti virus filtering, spam filtering, content filtering, and encrypted email solutions. The company also provides vulnerability defense solutions, which include internal/external scanning, remote assessment, Web site monitoring, anti-phishing services, and anti-pharming services; and system defense solutions, such as host intrusion detection and prevention, remote backup and recovery, user auditing and alerting, policy compliance, and system virus and spyware protection. In addition, it offers user defense solutions, including Web content filtering, esecurity training, security awareness training course topics, Web-based learning, remote access, and identity tokens; and network defense solutions, which include network connectivity, help desk, and managed VPN/WAN. Further, the company\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s Archive Manager delivers the level of Federal Rules of Civil Procedure (FRCP) compliance capabilities. It offers its services on a subscription basis in the areas of vulnerability defense, intrusion defense, network defense, email defense, system defense, and user defense. The company offers its services through a pre-integrated platform and Web portal. It serves channel partners, network service providers, financial services, health care, and non-profit sectors. Perimeter eSecurity, Inc. was formerly known as Perimeter Internetworking Corp. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EThe company was founded in 1997 and is based in Milford, Connecticut.\u003C/p\u003E",
